03/10/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Local prosecutors have pressed charges against former Transport and Telecommunications Minister Marija Raseta-Vukosavljevic and six of her former associates for abuse of office in connection with a Belgrade Airport reconstruction project. The spokesperson for the state public prosecutor's office, Tomo Zoric, announced the charges on Friday (October 1st). The defendants are suspected of embezzling 14,000 euros and could face up to 12 years in prison. 
Raseta-Vukosavljevic, who served as Serbian transport minister from 2000 to 2003, has denied any wrongdoing. (Tanjug, B92, SEEbiz - 01/10/10) 
